parsedData.name: Abhinav Sivanandhan

description: Architected a service-oriented architecture-based assistive AI solution into the field service applications of three business units using Visualforce, Apex, Lightning Web Components (LWC), and Aquant.io API, streamlining workflows and enhancing user engagement.

Led a team of six to automate sandbox refreshes using Java, TestNG, Selenium, and SauceLabs, to reduce turnaround time by 95% and increase refresh frequency by 70%, maintaining integrations and managed services.
Developed automated data entry workflows for Stryker Europe Field Service using Lightning Web Components, significantly reducing manual errors and optimizing SOQL query performance by up to 90%.

Executed the migration of CI/CD pipelines from Atlassian BitBucket to Azure DevOps, restructuring code into a digestible format with near-zero downtime, significantly reducing operational costs and developer effort.

Resolved 80+ critical regression bugs and collaborated cross-functionally with project and governance teams to lead 25+ production releases as a DevOps Engineer, utilizing Salesforce DX, Git, and Azure DevOps.

Performed ITIL Service operations, including resource provisioning, Identity and Access Management (IAM), bulk data loads (Data Loader, Workbench, Future Apex - up to 2.5M records), environment troubleshooting, code migration, static code analysis (SonarQube, PMD), technical governance, change management (ServiceNow), process optimization, and technical debt reduction (13/56 KPIs) while adhering to SLAs.

Modified legacy workflows to Salesforce Flows and developed a Flow error logging and graceful degradation framework to enhance reliability.  Also contributed to a logging framework to monitor and manage governance limits using utility classes that query the log object and trigger alerts for visualization of inefficient usage.

Devised a batch scheduler using machine learning and optical character recognition (React, AbbyCloud,Python) to validate 20,000 product labels, reducing 5,000 hours of manual effort and preventing critical shipping delays.

Designed a monitoring system in the SFDC org using asynchronous Apex, SOAP API-based web services and Streamlit(Python) to govern development, data loads and access control to ensure compliance and oversight.
Deployed an open-domain chatbot using Flask-based RESTful APIs to Heroku, achieving 80+% accuracy.

projects: Developed an LLM-powered marketplace with a priority-based checkout system, integrating a queueing system for asynchronous task processing and an RAG Chatbot for enhanced product retrieval.  Deployed to AWS.

Built a serverless, event-driven GraphQL-based microservices backend for a social media application for artists, featuring a personalized recommendation system and seamless cloud-based media management.
Designed a scalable image classification platform with container orchestration, dynamic scaling, and self-healing, achieving 28.54 transactions/sec, 99.68% availability, and a 0.35s response time.
